The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, had phone conversations with the President of Cyprus, Nicos Anastasiades, and the Turkish Cypriot Leader, Mustafa Akinci. Pence expressed the United States' strong support for the Conference on Cyprus happening in Switzerland and urged both leaders to take advantage of this historic opportunity to reunify the island. He expressed confidence in their ability to secure a settlement that would reunify Cyprus as a bizonal, bicommunal federation, benefiting all Cypriots.